      • getUniqueFilename

        public String getUniqueFilename(String baseFileName,
                                String extension,
                                boolean cleanBaseFileName,
                                String... ancestorFolders)
        Returns a unique file name
        Parameters:
        baseFileName - the requested base name for the file
        extension - the requested extension for the file
        cleanBaseFileName - specify if the baseFileName has to be cleaned before being used (i.e. 'jboss-web' should not be cleaned to avoid '-' to become '_')
        ancestorFolders - specify the ancestor folders for the file (if there's no ancestor folder, just pass 'null' value)
        Returns:
        a String representing the unique file generated
